---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Puppy Tips - Life with Yukki"
  description="Helpful tips and advice for raising a Shiba Inu puppy"
  alternateUrls={{ en: '/tips/', ru: '/ru/sovety/' }}
>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Puppy Care Tips</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">Lessons learned from raising Yukki</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tips-container">
        <!-- Example tip -->
        <article class="tip-card card">
          <div class="tip-icon">üêï</div>
          <h2>Understanding Shiba Inu Personality</h2>
          <p>
            Shiba Inus are known for their independent and spirited nature. They're incredibly
            smart but can be stubborn. Early socialization and consistent training are key to
            raising a well-behaved Shiba.
          </p>
          <ul class="tip-list">
            <li>Start training early (8-12 weeks)</li>
            <li>Use positive reinforcement techniques</li>
            <li>Be patient and consistent</li>
            <li>Respect their independent nature</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="tip-card card">
          <div class="tip-icon">üçñ</div>
          <h2>Nutrition & Feeding</h2>
          <p>
            Proper nutrition is crucial for your Shiba Inu puppy's growth and development.
            Choose high-quality puppy food and establish a consistent feeding schedule.
          </p>
          <ul class="tip-list">
            <li>Feed 3-4 times daily for puppies under 6 months</li>
            <li>Choose age-appropriate high-quality food</li>
            <li>Avoid overfeeding to prevent obesity</li>
            <li>Always provide fresh water</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="tip-card card">
          <div class="tip-icon">üéæ</div>
          <h2>Exercise & Play</h2>
          <p>
            Shiba Inus are energetic dogs that need regular exercise and mental stimulation.
            A tired Shiba is a happy Shiba!
          </p>
          <ul class="tip-list">
            <li>Daily walks (at least 30-60 minutes)</li>
            <li>Interactive toys for mental stimulation</li>
            <li>Supervised playtime with other dogs</li>
            <li>Safe, enclosed spaces for off-leash play</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="tip-card card">
          <div class="tip-icon">‚ú®</div>
          <h2>Grooming Essentials</h2>
          <p>
            Shibas have a double coat that requires regular maintenance, especially during
            shedding season (which happens twice a year).
          </p>
          <ul class="tip-list">
            <li>Brush 2-3 times per week (daily during shedding)</li>
            <li>Bathe every 3-4 months or as needed</li>
            <li>Trim nails regularly</li>
            <li>Clean ears weekly</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      color: var(--color-primary);
      font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    }

    .page-subtitle {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
      color: var(--color-text-light);
    }

    .tips-container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(380px, 1fr));
      gap: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .tip-card {
      transition: transform var(--transition-base);
    }

    .tip-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-4px);
    }

    .tip-icon {
      font-size: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    }

    .tip-card h2 {
      color: var(--color-primary);
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    }

    .tip-card p {
      color: var(--color-text);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .tip-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .tip-list li {
      position: relative;
      padding: var(--space-sm) 0 var(--space-sm) var(--space-xl);
      color: var(--color-text-light);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .tip-list li::before {
      content: 'üêæ';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: var(--space-sm);
    }

    /* Placeholder styles */
    .tip-placeholder {
      padding: var(--space-2xl);
      text-align: center;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-secondary-light) 0%, var(--color-secondary) 100%);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      min-height: 200px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .placeholder-icon {
      font-size: 4rem;
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
      opacity: 0.5;
    }

    .tip-placeholder h3 {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .tip-placeholder p {
      color: var(--color-text-light);
      font-style: italic;
      margin: 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .tips-container {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
